<strong>Product Specialist</strong></p>
<p>
You will support product managers who are responsible for building killer software products for musicians. As a <strong>Product Specialist</strong> on the ReverbNation team, you must be comfortable dealing within a fast-paced, performance-driven startup and be able to manage priorities effectively.</p>
<p>
This position is an awesome opportunity for a technical/web loving candidate working towards a long career in the product management field. You will be required to put in the time, commit to the work and put in the extra effort to build your skills. In return, you will receive the rare mentorship opportunity to learn from some of the most talented product managers and senior leadership in the Triangle, on the latest, cutting edge technologies and in a rapidly growing start up environment.&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>
<p>
<strong>In this position, you will&hellip;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Support a product team in the development of new products and the maintenance of existing ReverbNation products</li>
<li>
Participate in status updates with your product and development team</li>
<li>
Develop, analyze and deliver reports on product performance</li>
<li>
Manage KPIs for several ReverbNation products</li>
<li>
Participate in QA activities of all products and services that are released to the site</li>
<li>
Coordinate integration projects with external partners</li>
<li>
Research competitors and best practices</li>
<li>
Crank out work (headphones) as well as communicate with others (meetings)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>You will have&hellip;</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
2+ years of experience in the web technology field</li>
<li>
2+ years of product or project management responsibilities</li>
<li>
Strong quantitative abilities and/or experience with web analytics tools</li>
<li>
Bachelor&rsquo;s degree</li>
<li>
Have familiarity with technical aspects of web development (any hands on HTML / CSS experience is a big plus)</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>In return, you&#39;ll get...</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
The satisfaction of watching your friends use your work when they&#39;re out in public</li>
<li>
The opportunity to work with some of the most talented designers, developers and leaders in the Triangle</li>
<li>
Great benefits package that includes company paid healthcare plans, 100% company paid dental and vision, 401(k) match, continued education reimbursements,18 PTO days/year + 7 company holidays</li>
<li>
A new hoss of a machine and leather executive chair with lumbar support</li>
<li>
Very casual work environment where jeans, tees and sneakers are encouraged</li>
<li>
Regular company outings with your awesome co-workers that include Bulls games, cookouts and Reverb hosted house parties</li>
<li>
Great office location in Durham that is walking distance to lots of local restaurants and shops</li>
</ul>
