			<description><![CDATA[<p>
As a <strong>Graphic Designer and Marketing Specialist</strong> at ReverbNation, your primary responsibility will be the visual execution of various corporate marketing and branding initiatives. These projects will consist of, but will not be limited to, web and email design, online and traditional printed banners, fact sheets, flyers, posters and advertising materials. You will be responsible for maintaining the ReverbNation brand and extending the corporate style guide as necessary.</p>
<p>
While the bulk of assignments in this role will center on graphic and web design responsibilities, this person will also perform various marketing tasks to support other marketing initiatives. These assignments may include creative concepting, marketing research, public relations strategies and social media responsibilities. This position will report to the Director of Marketing and also help support the marketing team on various projects and assignments.</p>
<p>
<strong>Required Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
A graphic or web design degree</li>
<li>
1+ years of professional experience in a graphic design capacity</li>
<li>
Proven experience and with the entire Adobe Creative Suite</li>
<li>
Understanding and experience with HTML and CSS</li>
<li>
Traditional graphic design and print production knowledge/training</li>
<li>
Experience managing and coordinating various projects simultaneously</li>
<li>
The ability to self-organize, prioritize, multi-task and work against multiple deadlines in a fast-paced environment is essential</li>
<li>
Some experience with marketing writing and editing</li>
<li>
Strong analytical and critical thinking skills</li>
<li>
Exceptional personal writing and presentation skills are a must</li>
<li>
Must be proficient in Excel, PowerPoint, and market software tools</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Nice to have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Experience with motion graphics and video editing a plus</li>
</ul>
<p>
This position reports to the Director of Marketing and is a <u>3-month temp-to-hire opportunity</u>. If you are confident in your abilities, up for a good challenge, and ready to start your career working with a growing start up in the technology and music industry &ndash; send us your resume and tell us why you are awesome.</p>
