			<description><![CDATA[<p>
<strong>CONTENT MARKETING AND COMMUNITY MANAGER</strong></p>
<p>
ReverbNation is currently hiring for an articulate, motivated, assertive, and skilled marketing professional to become our <strong>Content Marketing and Community Manager</strong>. This hands-on position will report to the Director of Marketing and manage all of the company&rsquo;s content marketing efforts and social media outreach as well as participate in public relations initiatives.</p>
<p>
<strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Take complete ownership of all ReverbNation social media and inbound marketing efforts and strategy. You will be expected to not only execute but also guide and develop opportunities and ideas for new engagements.</li>
<li>
Manage social media campaigns and day-to-day activities. Duties include recognizing opportunities for online advocacy, drafting editorial, community-outreach efforts, posting on relevant blogs, and seeding content into social applications as needed.</li>
<li>
Become an advocate of the company in social media spaces, engaging in dialogues and answering questions where appropriate.</li>
<li>
Establish and monitor effective benchmarks for measuring the impact of content marketing and social media programs, and analyze, review, and report on effectiveness of campaigns in an effort to maximize results.</li>
<li>
Deliver regular feedback on insights gained from social media monitoring to the marketing and product management teams, to help evolve strategies.</li>
<li>
Manage the company blog including writing original posts, editing posts by others and scheduling guest posts.</li>
<li>
Monitor trends in social media tools and applications and provide subject matter expertise to the marketing team, effectively guiding future growth of ReverbNation&rsquo;s social media involvement.</li>
<li>
Synthesize large amounts of data into actionable information to ultimately make better-informed decisions regarding all social media and content marketing efforts.</li>
<li>
Work with the marketing and product development teams to draft press releases, pitch story ideas to media and serve as a liaison to company spokespeople. In addition to this you will also:
<ul>
<li>
Coordinate formal outreach</li>
<li>
Identify appropriate channels for engagement of executives</li>
<li>
Manage the press center, while updating company information</li>
<li>
Encourage adoption of relevant social media techniques into the corporate culture and into all of the company&rsquo;s products and services</li>
</ul>
</li>
<li>
Foster great working relationships with all levels within the company and across multiple disciplines.</li>
<li>
Apply a combination of humor and appreciation for fun with an integral drive to continuously improve and contribute to the ReverbNation and marketing team.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Required experience and skills:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
1+ years of professional experience in a community management, social media or content marketing role</li>
<li>
Undergraduate and/or graduate degree in marketing, communications, journalism or public relations is required.</li>
<li>
Proven experience working in a corporate content marketing and/or social media marketing position with solid understanding of how social media can be used to accomplish/improve given business objectives.</li>
<li>
Strong project management and organizational skills.</li>
<li>
In-depth knowledge and understanding of social media platforms and their respective participants (Facebook, Twitter, Hootsuite/Tweetdeck, Google+, Youtube, Pinterest, etc.) and how they can be deployed in different scenarios.</li>
<li>
Thorough knowledge of public relations methodology and AP style.</li>
<li>
Team player, with the confidence to take the lead and guide others when necessary.</li>
<li>
Strong technical understanding and ability to pick up on new tools quickly.</li>
<li>
Excellent writing skills and a willingness to use them.</li>
<li>
Superior verbal communication skills and powers of persuasion.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Bonus points for:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
Knowledge of blogging ecosystem relevant to the music industry a plus.</li>
<li>
Knowledge/experience with HTML, WordPress, Google Analytics.</li>
</ul>
<p>
<strong>Caution to all applicants:</strong><br />
This is not a position for those interested in tweeting to cool bands and updating our Facebook status.&nbsp;We are interested in experienced applicants who are students of content marketing trends and social media best practices and have a genuine passion and insatiable curiosity in this field. We want someone who can actively demonstrate the value of content and social media marketing and constantly drive to improve engagement with our customers. If your long-term goal is to be a CMO someday and currently understand what &ldquo;content marketing&rdquo; means for our business, please send your resume today.</p>
]]></description>
